The Commodity Credit Corporation hasaccepted a bid for an export bonus to cover a sale of 12,500tonnes of wheat flour to Iraq, the U.S. AGriculture Departmentsaid.    The bonus awarded was 113.0 dlrs per tonne and will be paidto Peavey Company in the form of commodities from CCC stocks.    The wheat flour is for delivery May 15-June 15, 1987, thedepartment said.    An additional 162,500 tonnes of wheat flour are stillavailable to Iraq under the Export Enhancement Programinitiative announced January 7, 1987, USDA said. Reuter&#3;